@comment{
  Add your publications below. Jekyll-Scholar renders them on /publications/.
  Your name (Zou, Jiatuo) is bolded automatically via the scholar: config in
  _config.yml. To feature a paper on the homepage, add  selected = {true}.
  For a thumbnail, add  preview = {img.png}  and place the image in
  assets/img/publication_preview/.

  Example of an under-review paper (copy it outside this comment block, then
  uncomment and edit):

  inproceedings{zou2026yourkey,
    title     = {Your Paper Title},
    author    = {Zou, Jiatuo and Coauthor, A. and Advisor, B.},
    booktitle = {Under review},
    year      = {2026},
    abstract  = {One-paragraph summary of the work.},
    selected  = {true}
  }
}
